- All colors must come from variables defined in `:root`.  

- Prefer global styles when they can be reused across modules.
- Only create local styles if they are specific to a single module or component.

- Do not use !important unless it is strictly necessary and justified.

- Maintain a clean and consistent class structure. Avoid duplication and unclear naming.